                'When setting up a company in Ireland, the Constitution is the foundational legal document for your business, replacing the traditional MoA and AoA for most Private Limited Companies (LTDs) under the Companies Act 2014.',
                'It outlines the companys name, states that it is a private company limited by shares, and specifies the internal rules governing its structure and operations. For LTDs, there is no "objects clause" limiting the companys activities; it has the same contractual capacity as a natural person.',
